A solid 5/5   

"Being happy is the easy part , staying happy is what people struggle with. "  


The answer is no is written by Fredrik Beckman who is definitely one of my favourite authors. He knows both human and humor very well .

This short story by Fredrik Beckman is a witty and comforting piece . The hilarious take on humans and problems in staying happy is what the author discovers . 

Lucas is a grown man who loves staying alone . He does not  like people and tries to prevent meeting with new people as much as possible . As much as he hates humans he also cannot say no to them because although he doesn’t like making friends he surely doesn’t want enemies as well .A series of events unfolds when a frying pan is found lying on the streets and Lucas is questioned about it .

This story deals with Lucas trying and failing to avoid humans and at the same time discovering human nature in general . He meets new people , understand other humans and the most unexpected of all try to advice people and at the end protects his solitude at all cost.

The author is definitely an expert in writing a hilarious piece without even naming or describing more than half characters to form a plot , he can call them by head 1 , head 2 or even by the colour of their dress just to avoid naming them which makes him sound like a little bit of Lucas only and that is what makes it a hilarious ride and at the same time present the humaness(if that is an actual word) , love and desperation people hold in them .
